The never walk alone will field two playing squads
simultaneously, with Villa Park encounter taking place on December 17 and Club
World Cup semi in Qatar the next day. Meanwhile Jurgen Klopp threatened
to pull out of the competition, after beating Arsenal 5-4 on penalties. Tuesday, December 17 is scheduled for the Carabao
Cup quarter-final tie between Aston Villa and Liverpool by 7.45pm. Liverpool would have to play two games with just 24
hours spacing.